create two foldes client & server

inside client ->
npx create-react-app ./
(npx create-react-app client) // if folder not created before

inside server ->
make a new file index.js

- in index.js import all the libraries
- add "type": "module", in the package.json to import using the 
import statement and not the require statement. 

- add 
"scripts": {
    "start": "nodemon index.js"
  },

for the auto reload using nodemon

in client ->
npm install axios moment react-file-base64 redux redux-thunk react-redux

in server ->
npm install express body-parser nodemon cors mongoose

mongoDB
mongodb+srv://sarthak100:<password>@cluster0.8kako.mongodb.net/<dbname>?retryWrites=true&w=majority

// const CONNECTION_URL = 'mongodb+srv://sarthak100:sarthak100@cluster0.8kako.mongodb.net/<dbname>?retryWrites=true&w=majority';
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5000;

### How to deploy.
Make a .env file, add mongodb connection url to it.
remove PORT from .env, Heroku will add it itself
Don't include .env to .gitignore.
Do git init inside server folder.
Make a Procfile inside server folder, and add a web start point.
Follow the steps on the heroku website.
Deploy server to Heroku.

Go to client/src/api/index.js
change the url to that of the heroku one.
Now inside the client folder do npm run build.
We will deploy on netlify without uploading to github.
Drag the build folder to the netlify to deploy it.

server -> https://mernstackcrudapplication.herokuapp.com/
client -> https://mernstackcrud.netlify.app/